---
title: "Demonstrating a Pragmatic Solution to Context Associations in RDF Using Blank Node Graphs"
date: 2025-06-03 00:01:00 +0800
selected: false
pub: "22nd Extended Semantic Web Conference (ESWC)"
# pub_pre: "Submitted to "
# pub_post: 'Under review.'
pub_last: ' <span class="badge badge-pill badge-publication badge-info">Demo</span>'
pub_date: "2025"

abstract: >-
  The paper proposes a pragmatic approach for modeling contextual associations in RDF by introducing the <a href="https://w3id.org/context-associations/specification" target="_blank">RDF context associations specification</a>, which uses Blank Node Graphs to ensure clear, interoperable handling of contextual information such as provenance, confidence, and policies across web data ecosystems. A <a href="https://knowledgeonwebscale.github.io/rdf-context-associations-demo/" target="_blank">demonstrator</a> illustrates how this model supports contextual data representation and SPARQL-based filtering.
keywords: Linked Data, RDF, Context Associations, Blank Node Graphs, Personal Data

